skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "7992c68f-7198-4c02-a5de-b432b34a2a49", "value": "A metal disc before it is stamped to become a coin."}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "ca1ab2f2-6a94-4536-b532-b0d9e1ef2591", "value": "FISH Archaeological Objects Thesaurus"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "07493aeb-5ad0-442e-95f4-d52a1261c418", "value": "Originally developed by the Archaeological Objects Working Party and published by the mda. It provides guidance for the recording of archaeological objects in Britain and Ireland covering all historical periods. Now maintained by FISH on behalf of the heritage sector"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "0f3b9849-46b9-4173-9a0d-3bf78d3c3f12", "value": "A piece of metal, usually cast, struck or stamped, with a definite value."}
{"id": "d0de8a56-dcde-48c8-8861-7028e3f25d12", "value": "A woven fabric used to trim clothes."}
{"id": "32d384d7-f988-4e7f-a6b2-b445abb5f2c8", "value": "Woven material."}
{"id": "f32daa7c-cdcb-447b-a391-b3b32584f498", "value": "A handheld weapon that fires missiles by means of explosives."}

{"id": "0dc15cac-390c-437c-9d42-a533c5ccc8d1", "value": "A flask holding gunpowder used to prime a firearm, ie to provide a small quantity of gunpowder to be put in the pan which would be lit to set off the main charge in the barrel. The powder would often be a finer grade than that used for the charge."}
{"id": "0057ed04-eb0e-40b7-9701-460fdf548402", "value": "A mortar used specifically for grinding cosmetics."}
{"id": "366fe81c-1c5e-4970-bbe6-a8eb8c71f899", "value": "A mixing or grinding vessel."}
{"id": "7c828c6a-1bb2-46b7-93a7-6847b46f0e98", "value": "A pestle used specifically for grinding cosmetics."}
{"id": "b060aac6-e5d6-4f37-b8d1-4c94d17afeb2", "value": "A flat heavy slightly curved blade."}
{"id": "93c6d2ac-b57a-473f-9c89-336d7f60256c", "value": "A long narrow two edged sword with a guarded hilt, used as a thrusting weapon."}
{"id": "8b05d0a6-cbad-4a13-83f2-5b985a7c7bb8", "value": "A broad design of sword used for cutting and slashing."}

{"id": "4a1a3577-7374-4e7a-b38f-a507dc178fce", "value": "A cutting and thrusting weapon consisting of a blade and a hilt. The blade varies in length and width and the cutting edge can vary from being purely the point to being one or both sides or a combination of these."}
{"id": "d1ed2620-caca-4092-90db-8fa9455a9552", "value": "A two edged broadsword."}
{"id": "d41914ec-36d6-42df-ba8f-089d756c5459", "value": "A belt worn around the waist from which a sword is hung. Where worn over the shoulder use baldric."}
{"id": "247a6ed9-8987-4625-87f5-c32d2ad919f5", "value": "A sash or belt worn over the shoulder to the hip for carrying a sword."}
{"id": "5690f1e8-ff56-4a3b-aee4-344ae755d07b", "value": "A curved sword designed to cut with used by cavalry."}
{"id": "5ccff9fb-9f6a-445b-ae99-0ecfd8b5a42a", "value": "A single edged sword."}
{"id": "be497e42-72a6-4e9e-94fe-7889d2c4213d", "value": "A type of sword often used by infantry."}
{"id": "66c7be84-4b3c-4dca-9ca6-8b564645b3df", "value": "A fencing sword often used for recreational purposes."}
{"id": "6b95dbd4-a0b3-402a-8612-5add25cab897", "value": "A long spear designed to be thrown in order to injure or kill a given target."}
{"id": "471c3b04-22eb-4390-821b-5513d200ded0", "value": "A long wooden shafted weapon tipped with a metal point."}
{"id": "bfe0cc46-afc7-4dba-a1ed-78723847630a", "value": "A long spear used on horseback."}
{"id": "c6f8b240-fa17-4d31-8519-7b5c97255060", "value": "The blade or sharp-pointed head attached to the end of a spear's shaft."}
{"id": "2298c270-40e5-4643-8453-5a9ebdc21fc2", "value": "A long shafted weapon with a pointed head used for thrusting or as a missile."}
{"id": "88baaaf4-e9e8-4d98-8c18-305e947097db", "value": "Wax used to seal letters, envelopes, documents, etc."}
{"id": "094978c0-61bb-4002-b5ac-ff9269fb3f34", "value": "Semi precious stone or glass engraved with a design and used to make an impression on wax or clay."}
{"id": "eb3e4388-70f7-4d48-8428-128e997a447c", "value": "The object used to make impressions in wax as seals."}
{"id": "fad2ee6d-33be-453c-8beb-12005e97fd2f", "value": "The tool used to create a mark on pottery by the potter."}
{"id": "75cee163-aab8-4d78-b2bd-b3ede3e5f02f", "value": "An ancient Egyptian gem cut in the shape of a scarab beetle and engraved with symbols on its flat side."}
{"id": "660b1af8-fedb-4cc1-881e-97d43e278388", "value": "A stamp, made of clay or stone, used to mark bars of eye ointment."}

{"id": "1fab989d-aa04-4283-ae5e-e3bd71fdfce7", "value": "An object used for counting, keeping count or marking the position of a player in a game, usually in the form of a small circular-shaped piece of bone, metal, wood, plastic or other material."}
{"id": "42ad8a54-fee2-4308-a779-437f740de904", "value": "A marker used in the playing of a game."}
{"id": "f8ac4414-fe1e-481e-98ec-f020f1a7e2ab", "value": "A tube to produce drops of liquid."}
{"id": "ab9c014c-8c24-41ba-8e6c-fe6a1d5df7f1", "value": "A small shallow cup used in assaying gold or silver."}
{"id": "6e619498-cb3f-4b68-b6de-418a9c3dff18", "value": "A container used with an alembic as part of the distilling process."}

{"id": "ed50d3ca-4fcc-48a2-8f98-662d527bb1ad", "value": "A vessel used as the lower part of a distillation unit consisting of a round-bottomed vessel with walls sloping inwards towards the rim. Some examples may have an external flange to support the upper unit (ALEMBIC). (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "8b021cd5-bf16-4157-8b44-2639a30b0405", "value": "A type of retort used for distillation."}

{"id": "3b1d04d1-70c2-48f2-8a44-8760e7296fe1", "value": "A concave glass dish used to hold material for observation or experimentation; so named for its resemblance to the disc covering the face of a watch."}
{"id": "ce4c0613-6306-4f0a-8c12-c2fbfc725e2d", "value": "A container, usually square or rectangular, used in metal processing for separating metals one from another, usually silver from gold."}
{"id": "31b6cb6a-1e6a-4308-9de0-fa70616848a1", "value": "A glass vessel with a long tapering neck that is bent down. Used for distillation."}
{"id": "9a67af62-05c5-4112-81a6-d183cade0af5", "value": "A container in which substances are heated to high temperatures."}

{"id": "bc7aa165-fcc2-41ab-88bb-23ff8cdd3729", "value": "A deep, rectangular or oval, straight-sided vessel with an everted, crenellated rim, used to hold either wax for dipping candles or molten sulphur for dipping matches. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "0e907da1-85e5-4c85-95c5-33cee61d38fe", "value": "Containers used for industrial or scientific purposes."}
{"id": "94bed651-4140-4ca1-9ac9-7ea38cc4ce28", "value": "A container used to hold, store, examine or create medicinal substances such as ointments, medicines, drugs, pills, tablets etc."}
{"id": "da6236af-e439-4393-ab52-ebdf7cd02b79", "value": "A container used in the distilling process to catch the distilled liquid."}
{"id": "f2953c11-9c9f-4b2a-915d-d5a4f2173f8a", "value": "A large bottle, generally protected by a basket or box, usually used for containing corrosive liquids, etc."}
{"id": "a54366f4-1d30-4388-b2a6-204f7c5646c1", "value": "A small bottle for liquids."}
{"id": "64c20043-86e6-424d-8c51-fbb4107cd15c", "value": "A kind of scourge."}
{"id": "0c7fec59-4993-4fe1-9df2-29c3b45622e1", "value": "A form of whip or lash, often used for self mortification."}
{"id": "30741b06-070d-4871-a5a2-e4b017af3572", "value": "A flail used for the mortification of the flesh."}

{"id": "7a7a474e-57d3-4225-89c7-07294b61f8f0", "value": "Kingdom of living things, lacking chlorophyll, that obtain their food from organic matter, usually by absorption. They include mushrooms, moulds and yeasts."}
{"id": "042fe067-ec98-4975-97ad-9b00345a27ab", "value": "Use for the remains of any part of a plant."}

{"id": "9dcbe7c9-deea-4333-82c6-6d7ae8ad5dde", "value": "Use for the remains of internal parasites of vertebrates, including humans, such as flukes, tapeworm, including their calcified cysts, etc. Eggs of the nematodes Ascaris sp. (maw-worm) and Trichuris sp. (whipworm) are commonly reported."}

{"id": "4dea14d2-ba8d-4d30-b289-e250497b1996", "value": "Remains of parasitic or free-living worms of the phylum Nematoda, characterized as having slender, cylindrical unsegmented bodies. Cysts of Heterodera commonly occur archaeologically"}
{"id": "793b449d-88be-4057-8bbc-52f7b0833cc0", "value": "An object fixed to the door or floor to limit the amount a door can open."}
{"id": "5b7497a3-c8ea-4ce5-80b7-a6efd4a34f3e", "value": "A barrier used to close an opening, usually hinged and often hung within a supporting frame."}
{"id": "ca95aa65-c22a-47cd-9c1f-bac80048a717", "value": "Use for the remains of any part of a mammal, except for humans."}
{"id": "254a7947-8f24-445c-88c7-7efaec59fb39", "value": "Use for the remains of any part of a human."}
{"id": "5e627e12-4deb-4acb-ba19-601d4e65d105", "value": "A container for incense."}
{"id": "92fa8cfe-3db7-44f0-8cef-53c142ee3f49", "value": "Tongs used with incense."}
{"id": "46695404-7e7f-40c0-bf28-eebeea280881", "value": "A hand held instrument for producing a current of air for cooling the user. It is both a practical and a fashion item."}
{"id": "5d28aff7-be52-4d59-824d-d71e7f5fd203", "value": "A case designed to hold a fan."}
{"id": "ef17b1ed-f9c4-49d0-938f-c058c76ca789", "value": "An instrument used to compress a substance into a smoking pipe."}
{"id": "a26d5e53-1bf5-4dcf-9e09-d3dd08b25e9d", "value": "A pipe in which a substance is smoked."}
{"id": "caff518c-5160-4a30-944b-7f97669203f5", "value": "A key for winding a clockwork mechanism."}
{"id": "995d3e29-5814-4d6c-8db5-3e789caab872", "value": "An instrument for measuring time."}
{"id": "87579a3d-8975-454f-9dbc-64ea08abf04d", "value": "A projectile discharged from a weapon, usually a firearm."}
{"id": "0ed2f761-bdff-428a-ab16-6f390ba7af1b", "value": "A metal sphere, usually lead, fired from a musket. Often bound into a cartridge."}
{"id": "fe147446-c1fe-4b23-8744-722c41b565b6", "value": "A mould in which bullets or musket balls are cast."}
{"id": "c4e0f9b1-48c9-47ba-89fc-5891ac7be330", "value": "A holder for weapons, explosives and ammunition."}
{"id": "2ccd2bd1-84f7-43dd-95e8-f29cf59c513b", "value": "A holder for arrows."}
{"id": "379d1c76-24c5-4bb7-a119-f6abcfc009e6", "value": "A container in which weapons are put for storage and or transportation."}
{"id": "64f16427-6e28-43b3-92f2-6b89571e07e1", "value": "A container for loose gun powder. Sometimes with a regulator to release enough powder for one shot."}
{"id": "9791ed11-02d9-4ae1-87ad-2d8886bc3f9e", "value": "A horn containing gun powder used for priming a firearm."}
{"id": "d103710b-1b30-484b-920e-3c553ebbf9ea", "value": "A flexible holder for a bladed tool or weapon."}
{"id": "444a7eea-818f-42aa-b45d-c103d49523d4", "value": "A rigid holder for a bladed weapon."}
{"id": "66b81a06-654b-4431-99bf-4bcbdcdfaf4a", "value": "Articles used in charging guns and ordnance."}
{"id": "d80caff3-aacf-47b2-b8c8-c8b9dcff7baf", "value": "A horn used to hold loose gun powder for recharging firearms."}
{"id": "25f2eb64-6059-4a54-910d-836c999de082", "value": "A container used to hold ammunition."}
{"id": "dcca0d33-d133-43a5-a773-5f492fbe93ba", "value": "A cutting blade with handle used for food preparation and consumption."}

{"id": "f4f24dec-87c2-4107-b1d8-11797c9b98ba", "value": "A knife prior to undergoing the processes of sharpening or finishing, consisting of a single piece of metal from which the blade and tang have been shaped."}
{"id": "5d39ff3c-c4ea-4269-b127-c677f226c396", "value": "An object used to catch animals."}
{"id": "0ae70589-140d-4089-ab1d-b9f7985d9633", "value": "A missile consisting of a number of weights joined together by cord. The bolas entangles the legs of a target causing it to fall."}
{"id": "3d122325-a815-4b16-bd64-c0320b7fe9ac", "value": "A weapon for shooting arrows."}
{"id": "23778a7d-14d1-43b6-9a83-4b7e53826997", "value": "Equipment for the hunting and capture of animals."}
{"id": "9fc6d7c0-8314-4dbb-9764-c8253ae09e49", "value": "A long rope with a noose at one end for catching animals."}
{"id": "5149b372-2a13-45fd-8f32-241d3e99b79b", "value": "Equipment used on a bird of prey for hawking."}

{"id": "f8492b7a-14a7-40aa-a579-7aebf8cfe106", "value": "An object used to retrieve birds used in hawking. Consists of feathers tied to a rope, food is contained in the lure whilst training the birds."}
{"id": "23ac53f5-4317-4c17-9d8a-feb8155967ff", "value": "An unfinished, roughly shaped axehead."}
{"id": "217dd8dd-9093-4755-87b6-4d1ba61e636d", "value": "An intially worked object, prepared to be made into a final product."}

{"id": "75e1bd0c-a604-43c0-bed3-ca855337cb57", "value": "A piece of metal or wood, or other material used in the manufacture of an item, intended for further fabrication and therefore representing an unfinished object. Usually relates to objects manufactured in quantity such as coins, knives etc."}
{"id": "7dfeb567-9e7f-4c08-aec2-a703888a6ed0", "value": "An partly-worked millstone that is still to be finished."}

{"id": "98f0a0dc-9581-4b17-8d25-f0bb74544666", "value": "An iron bar or ingot of distinctive form with a pinched end previously thought to have been used as a medium of exchange in the Iron Age but is now believed to be a roughout for a sword."}
{"id": "b412d654-0c57-4d0e-8ac8-e3e6b8242dc6", "value": "An initially worked quern that is still to be finished."}
{"id": "4a805def-14b7-455e-906c-0eea0c2dfdb4", "value": "A flat surface often with drawers used for working upon."}
{"id": "182a824c-1f09-4ea7-aec9-96c97ad7fea3", "value": "A portable writing-case or surface, especially one for use on the lap. May contain compartments for storing writing materials and paper."}
{"id": "32947d88-fc48-4e7f-8c8f-308e24135933", "value": "An object which surrounds or makes up a keyhole."}
{"id": "58345eaa-6d5b-4b27-8a2c-0e6a93d14df2", "value": "A shaped rod which passed through a hole in the door and was used to raise a latch or to slide a bolt."}
{"id": "e432705b-84e8-43b9-a571-9b5d7843da38", "value": "A detachable lock with hinged loop used for attachment operated by a key."}
{"id": "cddb5243-35d2-4b5c-8050-7455dfeb1c9a", "value": "A device for operating a lock."}
{"id": "e165fe91-d983-4cf5-8167-942126df3ac2", "value": "A security device attached to objects."}
{"id": "ed0cc89a-3c67-470e-9096-e55de6d6d6a4", "value": "A bayonet designed to plug into the muzzle of a musket or rifle."}
{"id": "1ddefa09-d712-4a33-9771-d9de56ece64c", "value": "A bayonet designed to fit over the muzzle of a musket or rifle, allowing the gun still to be fired."}

{"id": "a49f0c79-6f26-433a-b89e-803222a21444", "value": "A short stabbing weapon, designed to be fixed to the muzzle of a musket or rifle, even in some cases to pistols. Some were designed to be used both fixed to long guns and independent of them."}
{"id": "78a750a4-82d4-4beb-a1ca-d5f485c0b328", "value": "Microscopic animal remains. Use more specific term if known."}
{"id": "fa133c0c-f1f3-4489-b4f7-230f19265fc5", "value": "Remains of any of the groups of animals characterized by having a bony or cartilaginous spinal column (backbone) and a well developed brain."}

{"id": "a4180ee1-7518-4e83-a4b6-70056ae371ec", "value": "Single celled marine organisms. Some form calcareous tests (shells). They are used archaeologically to study the nature of marine environments or establish the presence of marine conditions or products (e.g. imported seaweed)."}
{"id": "9c9788e2-5660-49d9-bae8-cbde77d2260b", "value": "Remains of one of the groups of animals characterized as lacking any form of backbone or spinal column."}
{"id": "449bfb96-8d6b-4e27-ba06-1acf478e9028", "value": "The remains of any part of any animal. Use specific term where possible."}
{"id": "13f5ada9-4964-4905-8b6a-a87b792b2541", "value": "Animal remains bearing evidence, such as knife marks on bones, that they were slaughtered and used for food."}
{"id": "ddf7aa3b-7287-4f65-a581-ad7add14ddc6", "value": "A tool, piece of equipment, container or other object used for or in fishing."}
{"id": "5c16ba28-9309-4782-9b8f-91a79f931409", "value": "A basket for the storage and transport of fishing equipment. For the storage and transport of fish use creel."}
{"id": "ac21792c-44ef-409a-a1ff-e39a0d2410f2", "value": "A wickerwork basket for holding fish or catching lobsters."}
{"id": "eb39bd71-daeb-424d-aa30-bb7e6e1f7ac6", "value": "Waste flakes and cores produced in the manufacture of stone implements."}
{"id": "97b3c327-9a7e-425c-939c-3e8d9551a6c2", "value": "A stone blade with one edge blunted."}

{"id": "91e060c9-5c93-4d0c-9b02-f1aac4551dfb", "value": "A flint blade with negative impressions of removals on one side of the dorsal surface, creating a crest. These constitute part of a previously worked striking platfom or result from preparing the flaked surface on a core before detaching flakes or blades."}
{"id": "cc3719b3-91bc-46ed-9530-28e9631d0b73", "value": "A struck piece of flint or other stone where the length is at least twice the width."}
{"id": "f4482c82-e5c9-4b27-a4eb-cec8c30be2fa", "value": "A stone grooved on one face thought to have been used to straighten and smooth arrow shafts."}
{"id": "1b43770c-4241-4449-82ff-ecd523cd5266", "value": "The weapon end of an arrow, often shaped for particular uses."}
{"id": "47009fbf-a395-4ae0-a377-876281181c29", "value": "A projectile fired from a bow."}
{"id": "35f52b36-3460-4658-a426-16cd6750cd3a", "value": "An Egyptian religious statuette."}
{"id": "9c8d24da-b3af-4c78-8242-32e2693f8556", "value": "A small carved or sculpted figure."}
{"id": "50b03813-31c7-4904-be69-1c3d1246013c", "value": "The burnt remains of a corpse."}
{"id": "b46c95c1-5937-4c8a-b3fa-ee2bcb2efd03", "value": "An urn containing a cremation burial."}
{"id": "6587d6db-ffd0-461b-8b45-8af8fc3a3b64", "value": "Use specific form where known."}
{"id": "48ebd614-5448-4bcc-b8f8-33f4eb6cd484", "value": "A fragment of the body of a vessel, or hollow object, usually of ceramic or glass. If known, use specific vessel type."}
{"id": "2626ccad-b24a-416c-ac96-d1655658fb45", "value": "A plug to keep out dust, moisture etc."}
{"id": "4ca3648b-74a4-4b3c-bdcc-c00ae7bd0ca0", "value": "An instrument with a series of pipes at different pitches, the air being produced by bellows, and pipes selected by keyboard or sliders."}
{"id": "6f8b2ea6-ed39-4473-9f3f-ef6500a954dc", "value": "A wedge shaped stone used in an arch."}
{"id": "a3179ab8-e764-4492-8892-c388b5af5333", "value": "The top stone of an arch which holds it all in place."}

{"id": "439a2d7f-964c-42fc-8a65-28f2d83938ef", "value": "The impost, or point at which a vault rests upon its support, and from which it seems to spring. Hence the term describes the bottom stone of a vault, which lies on the impost."}
{"id": "451f11c2-cec0-4521-9b95-37744b93d5eb", "value": "A long piece of timber, thicker than a board."}
{"id": "c06f7a88-21f9-42b2-9dc0-5e2ba5774501", "value": "A sawn piece of timber, thinner than a plank and often rectangular."}
{"id": "e62f9fa6-44b0-43fd-8051-fb343a889f9d", "value": "Part of a musical instrument."}
{"id": "39ea13e7-abe6-4c0c-babf-aa7eb42d02a4", "value": "Musical instruments by how the sound is produced by the instrument."}
{"id": "ac2f0144-ac27-425c-acb7-4c03d5300ca4", "value": "Use more specific term where available."}
{"id": "8bb6b3df-9a1d-4c58-9f9c-3d81ca822bb0", "value": "A case for the transportation and protection of musical instruments."}
{"id": "c8e54ead-5ef8-4ece-8631-c1223e33ea3a", "value": "Use for deposits formed by the action of the sea or under marine conditions."}
{"id": "b21f16ba-05ed-4de1-9e58-3261e3b12bf5", "value": "Use for deposits formed in estuaries."}
{"id": "75606d40-8f09-4299-94c9-ac68cec552d4", "value": "Algae usually found as a silica skeleton. They obtain their food by photosynthesis and are used in ecological reconstruction."}
{"id": "5ed7c98a-9aee-4b47-a304-5d2a5809cc91", "value": "A tool for pounding or grinding."}

{"id": "731410af-7952-4762-b7ab-eb0c86cba419", "value": "A cup with a rounded body beneath a deep neck. There may be a marked junction between neck and body and the angle of the neck may be inward-sloping, upright or everted. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "711d8676-84c7-4350-b737-c5017bf6c01e", "value": "A form of cup which incorporates a joke or conundrum, where cut-outs or holes in the body make conventional use impossible. The puzzle is how to drink from it without getting wet; usually achieved by sucking through a hollow rim or handle. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "1adcf893-8c39-4be1-beb8-e1fac7aeb1ef", "value": "A vessel composed of three or more separate compartments, joined together and pierced to allow liquid to flow from one to another. There may be one or more handles. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "71a5fdab-e3fe-4bf9-94b8-95fd36abf233", "value": "A cup with convex body walls. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "c7d91943-a15f-47cd-aa84-b7d87dce7abe", "value": "A small round dish on which a drinking vessel is set."}
{"id": "308859d5-e071-40c8-a3f8-d49048f05e7b", "value": "A cup with a marked change of angle in the body wall, generally at the point of maximum girth. (Source: MPRG)"}

(Source: SARC)"}
